[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "S:AJT82.AK82.Q2.T5 Q96.J964.T9.8642 74.Q73.AKJ73.KJ9 K53.T5.8654.AQ73"]
[BoardVersionToken "755824da85b38449c3d4509696e32235413f82a823823e44512976ceac117792"]
[Student "S"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/two_over_one"]
[Auction "S"]
1S Pass 2D Pass 2H Pass 2NT Pass 3NT Pass Pass Pass
{South opens 1\S.  
You respond 2\D, a 2/1 force to game.  Partner rebids 2\h, showing a 4-card side suit.

You don't have 4 \Hs, nor do you have have 3 \Ss. You do, however, have stoppers in \Cs so you bid 2NT. 
South happily says 3NT.}

